For the spicy green beans, heat the oil in a frying pan, add the beans, pepper and onion and fry for a few minutes until softened.Add the garlic and chilli flakes and fry for a further 3-4 minutes.For the sesame steak, thread each steak strip onto a cocktail stick and drizzle over the honey.Heat a little oil in a non-stick frying pan and fry the steak over a high heat for 4-5 minutes, or until cooked through and golden-brown.To serve, sprinkle the steak with sesame seeds and place onto a serving plate with the spicy green beans.